latestPosts.caption:
My husband wanted to try freediving, and since it’s a partner sport, he said, “Let’s do it together. You’ll have fun.” I said okay. Then we decided to do it during our honeymoon because we love doing activities together.

We trained for months, learning to swim and build confidence. When we flew out, the airline lost our only suitcase. We had packed everything in one bag, with just a small handbag, a phone, and a charger left. But we kept going.

Four months later, we were in the beautiful Mediterranean Sea. I swam from the shore to the middle of the sea with fins, feeling like a mermaid. The view, the fish, the calm—it was magical. 

I dived four times, each time going a little deeper. No tanks. Just breath-holding, trust, and small steps. I couldn’t have done it without my partner. @apneatotalmalta 

And I know one thing for sure. I’m coming back to Malta, this time to freedive even more.

latestPosts.caption:
Five years in Germany—this journey changed my life! ✨ I took my flight on March 11, 2020, and from that moment, everything was different. I spent a lot of time alone, discovered myself, and worked on my skills, mindset, and insecurities. I learned how to live alone, earn my own money, and pay my bills. I never really made friends on my own, but my husband introduced me to some amazing people.

After three years, I met my husband—a wonderful person I feel lucky to have in my life. I gave my whole heart to our journey together. 💕

Berlin, you will always be home. Forever in my heart. 🖤✨ #5YearsInGermany #BerlinForever #Growth #Love
